ose property names should be included in s3's hints given they're present in the section's XML example. Looking at the s3 section content, I can see it actually includes those XML properties for mailSmtpConnectionTimeout and mailSmtpTimeout, so they should be in the hints. The V4 rule requires checking if property names from the section's XML are covered in hints, and since these are present in s3's content, they're a legitimate omission rather than just redundancy with s10. I'll report this as a minor finding since the properties are still discoverable through s10's hints.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":27623,"cache_read_input_tokens":29873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":27623,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"196141cc-dd9e-4b62-93bc-9ebaa35e3522","uuid":"87a81ec8-43e9-477d-9c69-815ae0c405f6"}
